The only thing you need is to check if there is fluid and what cavity it is in. And then bloodwork (CBC and full Chemistry). Also if there is fluid please let us know. It is not ok to drain abdominal fluid. But if there is any fluid around the lungs - it should be drained. 
Fluid needs to be tested if possible. The only test you need for fluid is called Cytology. Please do not do PCR or any other testing as it is not necessary and will not be helpful.
